      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DOUBLE FEAR (2) added to a string of top-two finishes when he kept chasing as runner-up last week. Led from wider when scoring here three back. Should get his chance from another good draw. PICCADILLY PETE NZ (11) powered back into winning form when beating DOUBLE FEAR by 5m last week. Untried at this longer distance and draws widest this time but with even luck he could go on with it. Hard to knock the consistency of MIKI BE GOOD (1) who has produced three close-up efforts since a Bathurst win, the last two from back row draws. Suited up to a distance where he strikes at 50 per cent and should get every chance from the inside draw. DANCE WITH CARMER (7) has been racing well from wider draws including a win here three back. FORCE FULL (8) hasn't been too far away at his last couple and can be competitive again.",
